    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Generate contracts with HTTP / REST API and Airtable at scale\n\n**Pattern:** Document Generation · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nGenerate contracts with HTTP / REST API and Airtable at scale. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual ocr & extraction is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Download Source File → Parse CSV Contents → Clean & Reshape Rows → Rows Pass Validation? → Load Rows into Airtable → Stamp Processing Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to document generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating ocr & extraction in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "e1e93e45-5936-31a8-ef50-70f517943566",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "825dc330-cdd5-4efd-e31b-d5af10cc654d",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "57b11df5-7964-c50a-6b9a-f61390f3fc46",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your ocr & extraction process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
